definition:
A man of the tribe of Levi living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at Ezr.7.1; 
 son of: Seraiah (H8304H); 
 brother of: Jehozadak (H3087)
Aramaic of ez.ra (עֶזְרָא "Ezra" H5830) 
 § Ezra = "help"
 the priest and scribe who led the reforms of the returned exiles in Jerusalem; co-worker with Nehemiah
